1.Set up the project for version control and push to GitHub=>
> Create and navigate to your project folder:
  mkdir sample-project
  cd sample-project

> Initialize Git:
  git init

> Link to the GitHub repository:
  git remote add origin <Your GitHub link>

> Add and commit files:
  git add .
  git commit -m "Initial commit"

> Push to GitHub:
  git push -u origin main

2.Create, push, and manage branches=>
> Create and switch to a new branch:
  git checkout -b feature/update-readme

> Add "README.md" and commit:
  echo "Explain the project in brief." > README.md
  git add README.md
  git commit -m "Add README.md"

> Push the branch to GitHub:
  git push origin feature/update-readme

3.Merge changes into the main branch=>
> Switch to main:
  git checkout main

> Pull latest changes:
  git pull origin main

> Merge the feature branch:
  git merge feature/update-readme

> Push the merged changes:
  git push origin main

4.Clean up unused branches=>
> Delete the local branch:
  git branch -d feature/update-readme

> Delete the remote branch:
  git push origin --delete feature/update-readme
